quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  74,32,"No, indeed by the Moon"
  74,33,And by the night as it retreats
  74,34,And by the dawn as it shines forth
  74,35,Indeed it is one of the greatest
  74,36,A warning to humanity
  74,37,"To any of you who chooses to press forward, or to fall behind"
  74,38,Every soul will be held responsible for its deeds
  74,39,Except the companions of the right hand
  74,40,They will be in gardens. They will ask
  74,41,Those who were corrupt
  74,42,“What led you into hellfire?”
  74,43,"They will say, “We were not of those who prayed"
  74,44,“Nor were we of those who fed the indigent
  74,45,“But we used to speak vainly with vain people
  74,46,“And we used to deny the Day of Accountability
  74,47,“Until there came to us that which is certain.”
  74,48,Then will no intercession of intercessors profit them
  74,49,Then what is the matter with them that they turn away from advice
  74,50,As if they were affrighted animals
  74,51,Fleeing from a lion
  74,52,Still each one of them wants to be given scrolls spread out
  74,53,"By no means, but they are not conscious of the hereafter"
  74,54,"No, indeed it is a reminder"
  74,55,Let any who wills keep it in remembrance
  74,56,"But none will keep it in remembrance except as God wills. He is the Lord of righteousness, and the Lord of forgiveness"